Things that are both enjoyable and necessary or both unenjoyable and unnecessary virtually seldom exist.
seldom不常的, 稀少的 很少, 不常
we may prefer leisure times to work days, but the latter are indispensable.
indispensable不可缺少的, 责无旁贷的, 绝对必要的
It is true that television programs concerning personal lives of celebrities always receive the highest audience rating.
celebrity名声, 名人
and that autobiographies written by public figures are always on the top 10 best-sellers' list.
autobiography自传
In fact, it is the public, to a large extent, rather than mass media, that is paying too much attention on personal lives of celebrities.
extent范围, 程度, 区域
Most organizations of mass media industry, being inherently commercial, are driven by business motivations.
inherently 内在地, 生来地, 固有地
Television program producers, as well as columnists and writers, are always aware of what the public want to see, therefore tend to pander to tastes of the public. 
